{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T00:41:59.302Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Allowing \"I Don't Know\""},{"type":"text","text":" is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"single most effective anti-hallucination instruction"},{"type":"text","text":" — explicitly giving the model permission to admit uncertainty drastically reduces false information."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The key instruction:"},{"type":"text","text":" \"If you don't know the answer or are uncertain, say 'I don't know' — do not guess or fabricate information.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why \"I Don't Know\" Works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The Problem"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"AI hallucinations are not random — they happen when the model is unsure and your prompt does not give it permission to say so.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What happens without permission:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Model is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"unsure"},{"type":"text","text":" but no escape\n- Model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"guesses"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of admitting\n- Model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"fabricates information"},{"type":"text","text":" confidently\n- Result: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hallucinations"},{"type":"text","text":" that sound right"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The Solution"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The fix is to write a system prompt that explicitly rewards uncertainty.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicit permission"},{"type":"text","text":" — Model can admit uncertainty\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Rewards uncertainty"},{"type":"text","text":" — Honest answers preferred\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pattern established"},{"type":"text","text":" — Model learns to stop\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No guessing"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"I don't know\" instead"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The model had seen a new pattern: when something felt unfamiliar, instead of trying to grab onto some related concept somewhere nearby in embedding space and produce a plausible-sounding answer, it had permission to stop.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Core Instruction Template"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Basic Template"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The single most effective anti-hallucination instruction:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Answer the question below.\nIf you don't know the answer or are uncertain,\nsay \"I don't know\" — do not guess or fabricate information."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Minimal version:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don't have reliable information about a question,\nsay \"I don't know\" or \"I'm not sure\" clearly.\nThis is preferred to guessing."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Enhanced Template"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"More comprehensive:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Answer the question below.\n\nRULES:\n1. If you don't know the answer, say \"I don't know\"\n2. If you are uncertain, say \"I'm not sure\"\n3. Do not guess or fabricate information\n4. Only state facts you are confident about\n5. For anything uncertain, acknowledge uncertainty\n\nThis is preferred to guessing."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Document-Based Template"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"For grounding in provided documents:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<document>\n[paste your document, article, or data here]\n</document>\n\nAnswer the following question using ONLY the information in the document above.\nDo not use any outside knowledge.\n\nIf the answer is not in the document, say:\n\"This information is not in the provided document.\"\n\nIf you cannot find this information in the provided documents, say:\n\"This isn't covered in the provided materials\"\nrather than guessing."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicit Escape Hatch Template"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Give the model an 'I don't know' escape hatch.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"If you cannot answer this question confidently:\n- Say \"I don't know\"\n- Do not attempt to guess\n- Do not fabricate information\n- Do not use outside knowledge\n\nThis is better than providing incorrect information."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Advanced Techniques"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 1: Confidence Calibration"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Confidence calibration — 'Distinguish what you know with high confidence from what you are uncertain about. Use phrases like 'I'm certain that...' vs 'I think...' vs 'I'm not sure but...'\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"For each claim, indicate your confidence level:\n- High: I'm certain this is true\n- Medium: I think this is likely true\n- Low: I'm not sure, this may be incorrect\n\nIf confidence is low and you have no citation, return:\n- answer: I don't know\n- confidence: low\n- citation: none"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Output format:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"answer\": \"short answer or 'I don't know'\",\n  \"confidence\": \"high|medium|low\",\n  \"citation\": \"source or 'none'\"\n}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 2: Citation Requirement"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"For tasks involving long documents (>20k tokens), ask Claude to extract word-for-word quotes first before performing its task. This grounds its responses in the actual text, reducing hallucinations.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Answer the question and quote the specific passage from the document\nthat supports your answer.\n\nIf no passage supports it, say so.\n\nFor each claim:\n- Provide the exact quote\n- Note the source/section\n- Indicate confidence level"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 3: Explicit Rule for \"Don't Know\""},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Explicit instruction: Clearly tell the model what not to do or where it tends to go wrong. For example, your prompt could include phrases like: 'if you do not have a clear source for your response, say 'I don't know'.'\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"RULE: If you do not have a clear source for your response,\nsay \"I don't know.\"\n\nDo not guess.\nDo not fabricate.\nDo not use outside knowledge.\n\nOnly state facts you can verify."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 4: Labeling Training"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Teach models to say 'I don't know' when unsure by labeling truthful, false, and unknown statements.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example training:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Label each statement:\n- \"Richard Nixon was president.\" → true\n- \"Tom Hanks is an actor.\" → true\n- \"Zigabur Karbinski won the Pulitzer Prize.\" → I don't know\n\nInclude examples you completely made up and show that the correct\nresponse wasn't to guess—it was to say \"I don't know.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pattern established:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Familiar → Answer confidently\n- Unfamiliar → Say \"I don't know\"\n- Made-up → Say \"I don't know\" (not guess)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 5: External Knowledge Restriction"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Explicitly instruct Claude to only use information from provided documents and not its general knowledge.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"For factual questions, use only the information provided in the\nretrieved context.\n\nIf the context does not contain the answer, say:\n\"I don't have information about that in my sources\"\n\nDo not fall back on prior knowledge.\nDo not guess."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Real-World Examples"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 1: Document Question"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<document>\nAnnual Report 2024\nRevenue: $5.2M\nGrowth: 15%\nEmployees: 120\n</document>\n\nQuestion: What is the CEO's name?\n\nRULE: If the answer is not in the document, say\n\"This information is not in the provided document.\"\n\nAnswer:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Expected response:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"This information is not in the provided document.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"NOT:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"The CEO is John Smith.\" (hallucination)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 2: Factual Question"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Question: Who won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 2023?\n\nRULES:\n1. If you don't know the answer, say \"I don't know\"\n2. If you are uncertain, say \"I'm not sure\"\n3. Do not guess or fabricate information\n4. Only state facts you are confident about\n\nAnswer:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Expected response (if uncertain):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"I don't know\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"NOT:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"The winner was Dr. Jane Smith.\" (hallucination)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 3: Confidence-Calibrated Answer"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Question: What is the impact of intermittent fasting on longevity?\n\nAnswer format:\n- answer: <short answer or \"I don't know\">\n- confidence: <high|medium|low>\n- citation: <source or \"none\">\n\nRULES:\n- If confidence is low and you have no citation, return:\n  - answer: I don't know\n  - confidence: low\n  - citation: none\n\n- Distinguish what you know with high confidence from what you are uncertain about\n- Use phrases like \"I'm certain that...\" vs \"I think...\" vs \"I'm not sure but...\"\n\nAnswer:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Expected response:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"answer\": \"I'm certain that intermittent fasting improves metabolic health, but I'm not sure about direct longevity effects in humans\",\n  \"confidence\": \"medium\",\n  \"citation\": \"various studies on metabolic health\"\n}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 4: RAG-Based Question"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrieved context:\n\"The company's revenue increased by 15% in Q3 2024.\"\n\"Operating expenses were $2.3M.\"\n\nQuestion: What is the net profit for Q3 2024?\n\nRULE: If the context does not contain the answer, say:\n\"I don't have information about that in my sources\"\n\nDo not fall back on prior knowledge.\nDo not guess.\n\nAnswer:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Expected response:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"I don't have information about that in my sources\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"NOT:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Net profit was $1.5M.\" (calculated from hallucinated data)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 5: Training Examples"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt (with few-shot training):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Label each statement as true, false, or I don't know:\n\n- \"Richard Nixon was president.\" → true\n- \"Tom Hanks is an actor.\" → true\n- \"Zigabur Karbinski won the Pulitzer Prize.\" → I don't know\n- \"The moon is made of cheese.\" → false\n- \"Company X launched Product Y in 2023.\" → I don't know\n\nNow answer:\n\nQuestion: Who won the company's innovation award in 2024?\n\nRemember: When something feels unfamiliar, instead of trying to grab\nonto some related concept and produce a plausible-sounding answer,\nyou have permission to stop and say \"I don't know.\"\n\nAnswer:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Expected response:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"I don't know\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Explicitly Reward Uncertainty"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The fix is to write a system prompt that explicitly rewards uncertainty.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Say \"I don't know\" is preferred"},{"type":"text","text":" — Better than guessing\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reward honesty"},{"type":"text","text":" — Acknowledge uncertainty\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Don't penalize"},{"type":"text","text":" — No criticism for admitting"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Pair with Source Material"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The most reliable way to prevent hallucinations is to supply the source material and instruct the model to use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"italic"}],"text":"only"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" that material.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practice:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Provide sources"},{"type":"text","text":" — Documents, data\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Restrict to sources"},{"type":"text","text":" — No outside knowledge\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Combine with \"I don't know\""},{"type":"text","text":" — When not in source"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Verify High-Stakes Independently"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The most effective anti-hallucination techniques are: (1) give the model an 'I don't know' escape hatch, (2) provide source material and instruct it to use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"italic"}],"text":"only"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" that, and (3) verify anything high-stakes independently.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"For high-stakes:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Never use AI-generated stats directly"},{"type":"text","text":" — Without verification\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Treat output as starting point"},{"type":"text","text":" — Not final answer\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Verify independently"},{"type":"text","text":" — Check facts manually"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Match Approach to Stakes"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Match your anti-hallucination approach to the stakes.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Guidance:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Low stakes"},{"type":"text","text":" — Basic \"I don't know\" rule\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Medium stakes"},{"type":"text","text":" — Add confidence calibration\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"High stakes"},{"type":"text","text":" — Add verification, independent check"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5. Test with Unknown Questions"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Build a small eval set of questions that the model SHOULD NOT know: obscure facts, made-up names, recent events outside training cutoff, plausible-sounding but fake products. Run them through your prompt. Count how often the model says 'I don't know' vs invents an answer.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test set:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Obscure facts"},{"type":"text","text":" — Beyond training\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Made-up names"},{"type":"text","text":" — Fake entities\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Recent events"},{"type":"text","text":" — After cutoff\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fake products"},{"type":"text","text":" — Plausible but false"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Measure:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"I don't know\" rate"},{"type":"text","text":" — Good\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Invention rate"},{"type":"text","text":" — Bad"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"6. Toggle Rules for Evaluation"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Toggle the 'admit unknowns' and 'no hallucination disclaimer' rules. Generate the prompt.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Process:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test with rule"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"I don't know\" enabled\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test without rule"},{"type":"text","text":" — Rule disabled\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Compare"},{"type":"text","text":" — Measure difference\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Iterate"},{"type":"text","text":" — Adjust based on results"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"7. Use Chain-of-Thought Verification"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Chain-of-thought verification: Ask Claude to explain its reasoning step-by-step before giving a final answer. This can reveal faulty logic or assumptions.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Before answering:\n1. Think through what you need to know\n2. Identify what information you have\n3. Note any gaps in knowledge\n4. If gaps exist, say \"I don't know\"\n\nThen provide your best answer,\nflagging any parts where you're uncertain."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"8. Add \"Think\" Space"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"A crucial rule to remember when prompting LLMs is to give them space to 'think'. You don't want to overly constrain the model such that it can't explore various solutions.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Balance:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Allow thinking"},{"type":"text","text":" — Don't over-constrain\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"But give permission"},{"type":"text","text":" — To say \"I don't know\"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not too strict"},{"type":"text","text":" — Avoid micromanagement"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"9. Combine with Grounding"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Always allow the model to 'abstain' when uncertain and ground with retrieval or worked examples to reduce hallucinations.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practice:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Allow abstention"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"I don't know\" rule\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Ground with retrieval"},{"type":"text","text":" — RAG, sources\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Ground with examples"},{"type":"text","text":" — Worked cases"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"10. Iterate and Refine"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Toggle the 'admit unknowns' and 'no hallucination disclaimer' rules. Generate the prompt.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Process:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Start basic"},{"type":"text","text":" — Simple \"I don't know\" rule\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test"},{"type":"text","text":" — Run eval set\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Measure"},{"type":"text","text":" — Count \"I don't know\" vs guesses\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Refine"},{"type":"text","text":" — Add confidence, citations if needed"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Allowing \"I Don't Know\""},{"type":"text","text":" is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"single most effective anti-hallucination instruction"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"AI hallucinations"},{"type":"text","text":" — Happen when unsure, no permission to say so\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicit permission"},{"type":"text","text":" — Model can admit uncertainty\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Rewards uncertainty"},{"type":"text","text":" — Honest answers preferred\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pattern established"},{"type":"text","text":" — Model learns to stop"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Core instruction:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don't know the answer or are uncertain,\nsay \"I don't know\" — do not guess or fabricate information."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"7 best practices:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicitly reward uncertainty"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"I don't know\" preferred\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pair with source material"},{"type":"text","text":" — Use only provided info\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Verify high-stakes independently"},{"type":"text","text":" — Never use AI stats directly\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Match approach to stakes"},{"type":"text","text":" — Low/medium/high customization\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test with unknown questions"},{"type":"text","text":" — Measure \"I don't know\" rate\n6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Toggle rules for evaluation"},{"type":"text","text":" — Compare with/without\n7. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use chain-of-thought verification"},{"type":"text","text":" — Reveal faulty logic"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Advanced techniques:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Confidence calibration"},{"type":"text","text":" — High/Medium/Low levels\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Citation requirement"},{"type":"text","text":" — Quote supporting passage\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicit \"don't know\" rule"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear instruction\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Labeling training"},{"type":"text","text":" — Teach true/false/unknown\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"External knowledge restriction"},{"type":"text","text":" — Use only sources"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The most effective anti-hallucination techniques are: (1) give the model an 'I don't know' escape hatch, (2) provide source material and instruct it to use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"italic"}],"text":"only"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" that, and (3) verify anything high-stakes independently. These techniques won't eliminate hallucinations, but they dramatically reduce them.\""}]}]}}
